annotation.TEXT: So far, so good... Not much left of The Tower now.
Guess what? It's finally time to give this mode a try! That's right! It's No Death Mode time!
Okay, take this part very carefully...
Cakes Cakes Cakes...

Well, anyway, I could head straight to Space Station 2 first, but I actually want to wait and do that level second, for a certain reason. I'm going to do a different level first, and it's a short one that I shouldn't have any trouble with.
No spikes here!
So, yeah. That's the first of only a few trinkets that I intend to get. Also, I remember when the "Give Me A V" room used to trouble me, but I've gotten good at it now.

Okay, that's a weird graphical glitch that I don't think I've encountered before. I guess that occurs when you open up the pause menu while a "tutorial" message that touches the top of the screen is displayed.

Anyway, I opened up the pause menu just to show how long it took me to get back here with cutscenes enabled-- Less than nine minutes, which is good. Oh, and we still can't save in No Death Mode, obviously.
Demo count: 1
Fortunately, I know how to best get through $eeing Dollar $ign$.
Like with that choice leading to that trinket a moment ago, I'm used to taking the lower path here.
Demo count: 1
Well done!

Also, I wish there was a "Retry No Death Mode" option right there, so that you didn't have to go back to the title screen after each failure. Well, I hope you all enjoyed watching my No Death Mode attempts here. See ya!
NO!!! Darn it! I overshot the stinking platform there!
Really?! I seriously failed there?! ARGH!!!

Or did that graphical glitch a moment ago have something to do with the remaining conversations vanishing? Anyway, this is how I intended to handle this room the first time, which I think is an easier method.
Of course, you're also told that you can't save in No Death Mode on the screen where it asks if you want to disable the cutscenes.
Alright, can I traverse Space Station 2 without meeting a terrible, terrible death? We'll find out today!
And with that, Space Station 1 is complete!
Good. Now don't get Vitellary impaled...
Demo count: 1
Yeah, I'm skipping that trinket on the left there, which saves me a few tricky flips.
Ooh, the game lets you disable the cutscenes. Yeah, I think I'll do that. We don't want to waste time with those! Alright, let's get started!
Awesome!

Now, I'm not going to go for most of the trinkets, since I don't want to needlessly endanger myself. I definitely will collect the trinket in a certain room in Space Station 2 when I get there, though.
Okay, now I'll head to Space Station 2, which is to the left when I first exit the ship.
And I'm certainly skipping this trinket here, which requires dangerous precision movement.
Yeah, yeah, yeah. Enough talking. I just want to get to one particular conversation here.
Alright, now I've just gotta reach the exit myself, and I'm gonna do it... this way!
Woo! Made it! And with that, Intermission 1 is basically complete! I still have to get through this annoying room, but I can't die here.
Yeah, that was risky, but I'm so accustomed to going this way for the trinket in the Time Trials and practice runs, that I felt confident enough to do so here in No Death Mode too.
Yeah, all it takes is one stupid slip up to screw you over, and it can certainly happen in a room that you'd normally think wouldn't be a problem, like right there. Man...
...Darn it all! Yeah, either the game automatically disables the mid-intermission dialogue during No Death Mode anyway, or that graphical glitch earlier might've somehow screwed things up.
Just hold left through this room.
...Well, that totally just happened.

Could someone confirm for me whether or not it was that graphical glitch that affected the rest of the dialogue in this Intermission? Because I don't feel like redoing the first few levels in No Death Mode another time just to check that myself.
I wish I had thought of that sooner. Well, when this run is over, I'll see about getting back here in No Death Mode with the cutscenes enabled, which I should be able to do without too much trouble.
Alright, and from this point, it shouldn't be too difficult to finish Space Station 2!
Good. Now, the most difficult two rooms of this intermission are coming up next...
Yeah, yeah, yeah. Add those "?"s to the map. Couldn't there be a "skip adding things to map" option as well?
...Wait, shouldn't there be another conversation with my shipmate here? Oh, no. I hope the game didn't automatically disable the conversations for this intermission anyway!
Excellent! And, "Shenanigan" is fairly easy when you don't have to worry about dodging checkpoints.
Watch out. I wouldn't want to get smogged here.
Here we go...
Sorry, Viridian, but your life is more valuable than those way-too-risky trinkets right now.
Well, I hope you all enjoyed watching my attempt at No Death Mode!
Hey there, red guy. Let's go home.
Now, for this room, which was one of only three rooms that resulted in a death when I most recently went through the normal game while practicing for No Death Mode.
...Actually, I did that on purpose, just to show you guys what happens when you die in No Death Mode. You get a Game Over, and then it sends you back to the title screen.
Also, Violet said a line after the map display there. Did they forget to remove that line with the cutscenes disabled?
Yeah, that's where Vitellary would normally comment about the checkpoint. I'll have to get there in No Death Mode again with the cutscenes enabled.
No, man. I don't want to die.
(The other two rooms were The Gravitron, with 6 deaths, and Heaven's Gate in The Final Level, with 1 death, for a total of 8 deaths in that run.)
Oh, man. I think these three rooms are the hardest part of Space Station 1.
Yeah, nuts to you, Veni Vidi Vici!
Hello, and welcome back to VVVVVV!
Huh, isn't there normally another tutorial message here?
This room isn't too bad, if you know what to do.
I'm definitely super nervous right now, that's for sure.
Just hold right for these two rooms.
Let's try this for realsies this time! BTW, if you try moving the cursor over to "Save" on the pause menu, it'll tell you that you cannot save in No Death Mode.
Go through this little tunnel, then drop down, following the left wall.
Whoops, I didn't do this part quite as I intended. I should still be okay if I make the proper moves, though.
Okay, I'm back, and I'm now at Intermission 1 with Vitellary in No Death Mode, with the cutscenes enabled this time, as you can see.
However, I will definitely talk to him if I get to the point where he appears in The Laboratory later.
It is most definitely NOT perfectly safe!
Of course, it helps if I land in the proper spot.

In fact, my personal goal right now is to at least reach that particular SS2 room. (You know, the one with the trinket that's to die for in normal gameplay that's altered to make it reachable without dying in Time Trials and No Death Mode.)
Yes! The Tower is complete!
And yes, I know exactly where I'm going. I used the normal game to figure out exactly where to go to safely reach each of the four levels ahead of time.
Ah, here we are! Let's take on... The Tower!
I'm definitely going for that trinket!
Flip again there, walk until you enter a green room, then flip one more time, while still holding left, and you should end up entering Space Station 2 with no problem!
Wow, I'm always used to seeing 11 checkpoints in the top part of The Warning, but there are no checkpoints in No Death Mode!
Gotta be more careful. I wouldn't want to die in a stupid way. (Not counting that intentional demo one room in the first time.)
Pi is exactly 3!
Watch out for the spikes on the way to The Laboratory, but they shouldn't be an issue as long as you're paying attention.
Okay, we're good.
Whoa! Yeah, you kind of have to nearly get your head impaled there. Fortunately, it's just a matter of moving to the right at the right time.
And here we are! Get ready to bounce alright!
I believe I'll go to The Laboratory next, and the path leading to it is directly below the ship's entrance.
Alright, now where should I go next? I could go to either The Laboratory, or The Warp Zone.
Yeah, I think that method is better than going all the way back to the left.
Yes! Made it to this room! I still can't believe it's not butter! So, yeah. In Time Trials and No Death Mode, a row of spikes is removed so you can get this trinket without dying.
Oh, hey there, Vermilion. How's it going? Sorry, but I don't want to chat right now.
Let me think for a moment here...
Aim carefully here.
I'm just letting my Time Trial instincts take over for the moment here.
Whoa! That was close right there!
And I wanted him with me because he sort of leans on the fourth wall, commenting about a checkpoint he passes by during Intermission 1, and I want to see if that dialog changes in No Death Mode.
Hey there, yellow guy! Now, the reason I wanted to play Space Station 2 second, is so that Vitellary here would be with me in Intermission 1.
I'll follow the ceiling as much as I can right now.
Okay, now remember to flip to the lower conveyor at the screen boundary here. Otherwise, "LIES" will telefrag Viridian at the start of the next screen!
This level is certainly scary, but I think it is actually the easiest of the four levels available right now, especially since I'm not going for the trinkets.
Now, obviously, I'm not going for the trinket in the room above.
Keep holding left as you fall here, and you'll land in a "V". Then, flip from there while continuing to hold left.
Well, anyway. I'm here now, so let's see if I can avoid failing at "...Not as I Do" again.
Careful, don't rush too quickly into the Exhaust Chute room here!
Aw, I guess I still have to wait for the victory music here. Couldn't there have been a "skip level complete messages" option as well?
Oh, wait a minute, with cutscenes disabled, he's not going to actually converse with me during this intermission, is he? ...Nuts!
I'm definitely not going for the trinket in the room to the right. Way too dangerous.
I am soooo glad I don't have to bother with the underside of Gordian Knot, which gave me way more trouble than Veni Vidi Vici when I was trying to V-rank Space Station 2 in the Time Trials!
Alright, Vitellary, let's go home.
I believe I have to dodge the bus next...
These rooms aren't too difficult. Just play "Tapper" near the end of this room so your partner doesn't get impaled on the spike wall.
"A Deception" is a piece of cake (not a lie this time). But, be careful, as "Down Under" is still somewhat tricky.
Huh, so the game stopped for a moment to add the ship's location to the map there, but none of the time-consuming dialogue showed up, which is nice.
Well, that sucked, but at least I reached the "I Can't Believe You Got This Far" room, which was my primary goal here.
However, I still want to check out that other thing in Intermission 1 with the cutscenes enabled. Give me a moment here...
